Question: Do you think it is ok for the government to read your emails for counter-terrorism purposes?
Answer:
I do not think it is okay for the government to read my emails under the name of counter-terriorism. It intrudes my private life and deprives me of the sense of secuiruty for I am living under the supervision. After all, the ultimate purpose of counter-tourism is the subjective well- being of people . Furthermore, there are various ways to attack terrorism. Reading email is not the only option and it hurts public trust.